16 (2) 'Interest' means any right, title, or interest in and to a single-family dwelling or a
17 manufactured home community or mobile home park in Georgia.
18 (3) 'Prohibited business' means any partnership, corporation, or real estate investment
19 trust that manages funds pooled from investors, is a fiduciary to such investors, has a net
20 value or assets under management on any day during a taxable year, and holds a total net
21 value in all assets of $6,250,000.00 or holds interests in at least 25 single-family
22 dwellings in a single county. Such term shall not include a not for profit organization as
23 defined in Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code or a homebuilder.
24 (4)(A) 'Single-family dwelling' means real property or real estate where the only
25 substantial improvement to such real property or real estate in Georgia is a residential
26 single-family dwelling. Such term includes manufactured home communities or mobile
27 home parks and single-family dwellings split into two or more dwellings.
28 (B) Such term shall not include condominiums; townhouses; multifamily communities;
29 any unoccupied single-family dwelling acquired through foreclosure; or any
30 single-family dwelling that is not rented or leased and is used as the primary residence
31 of any person with an ownership interest in a prohibited business.
32 (b) A prohibited business shall not acquire an interest in any single-family dwelling in
33 Georgia."
34 SECTION 3.
35 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2025, and shall apply to any conveyance of an
36 interest in a single-family dwelling made on or after such date.
37 SECTION 4.
38 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
